The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Washington, June 29: The US Federal Reserve raised interest rates for a 17th straight time today and said more rises may be needed to curb inflation even after the now two-year run of credit-tightening. The central bank?s Federal Open Market Committee voted unanimously to lift the benchmark federal funds rate target a quarter-percentage point to 5.25 per cent, its highest level since March 2001. 

 Mumbai, June 29: Qualcomm is believed to have refused to cut royalty on CDMA chips used in handsets. Qualcomm chief Paul Jacobs today held an eight-hour meeting with Reliance Communications chief Anil Ambani.

 New Delhi, June 29: The Supreme Court today stayed a Gujarat High Court order directing detergent manufacturer Nirma to pay Rs 527.42 crore towards sales tax to the state government.

 Calcutta, June 29: R.S. Lodha, who has laid claim to the Rs 5,000-crore assets of the MP Birla group, and three of his associates were allowed exemption from personal appearance by a city court in connection with a criminal case.

 Calcutta, June 29: Bata India Ltd will re-introduce voluntary retirement scheme as well as undertake financial and operational restructuring this year.

 New Delhi, June 29: GAIL and Brazil?s Petrobras will jointly bid for the oil and gas exploration blocks in India.




